\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gkr1665702760703.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gkr1665702760703.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gkr1665702760703.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gkr1665702760703\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Developing Applications with Uniface\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Uniface IDE to create development objects, and then build them into Uniface archive files that are immediately deployed into a standalone test environment.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__topic_d20e1_d21e1_d22e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__p_d23e1_d24e1_d25e1\">Developing applications is an iterative process, so the following steps provide a high-level guide to the activities involved in developing a Uniface application.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d191e1_d192e1_d193e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Start by creating a Project to hold the Development Objects for your application. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d194e1_d195e1_d196e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create some Modeled Entities to define the application data and default behavior. These can then be reused in the components you create in the next step. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ffi1703160534674.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffi1703160534674.html\" title=\"Modeling is an activity in which you create abstract development objects that can be reused by other objects during development. Modeled objects are used to represent the application data, centralize business logic, define default behavior, and enforce consistency.\">Modeling the Application</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d197e1_d198e1_d199e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__p_d26e1_d27e1_d28e1\">Construct the application components for the user interface and business logic. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zrw1665702750469.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zrw1665702750469.html\" title=\"During the construction phase of application development activity, you create development objects that define the application components and runtime libraries needed for the application. Application components can reuse definitions that you created in the modeling phase.\">Constructing Components and Other Objects</a>.\n              The type of components you need depend on the type of application.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d200e1_d201e1_d202e1\">For web and mobile applications, use Dynamic Server Pages for the user interface and Services to handle backend processing. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nvu1665702750539.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nvu1665702750539.html\" title=\"You can use Uniface to develop, test, and deploy web-based applications. Web applications have unique requirements with regard to testing and deployment, state management and authentication, data maintenance, and security.\">Developing Web Applications</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"evi1665702676990.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/evi1665702676990.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to develop cross-platform mobile apps using dynamic server pages (DSPs), JavaScript APIs to access device functionality, and a third-party hybrid framework to package the app for Android and iOS devices. This makes it possible to develop the same code for all platforms, but take advantage of native functionality.\">Developing Mobile Apps</a>.\n               </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d203e1_d204e1_d205e1\">For desktop applications, us Form components for the user interface, Report components for printing, and Service components for business logic. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"shh1665702750613.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/shh1665702750613.html\" title=\"Enterprise desktop applications are distributed client/server applications—they allow users to retrieve and maintain data in a remote database using a locally-run application. Desktop applications are usually highly interactive, and provide a much faster response time than most web applications.\">Developing Desktop Applications</a>.\n               </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d206e1_d207e1_d208e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If necessary, create an Application Shell. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ohj1705472401504.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ohj1705472401504.html\" title=\"An application shell is a module used to initialize and run an application (Windows or character-based) or application server.\">Application Shells</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d209e1_d210e1_d211e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Build the application files. In the Project Editor of your project, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span>. This process automatically compiles components and library definitions and may package them into a deployable archive file (depending on your configuration). For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ery1665702625513.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ery1665702625513.html\" title=\"When Uniface development objects are compiled, the compiler checks the definition, syntax, and integrity of the object, inserts inherited ProcScript modules, resolves IncludeScript references and constant definitions, compiles the resulting code, and generates compiled runtime objects and descriptors. It can optionally generate files that show an object's ProcScript after inherited and included ProcScript has been resolved.\">Compilation</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d212e1_d213e1_d214e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Debug the application. The IDE includes a pre-configured deployment environment that you can use for unit testing and a Debugger to analyze problems. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fxt1665702750826.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxt1665702750826.html\" title=\"Uniface includes a pre-configured test environment that you can use for unit testing, and a Debugger to analyze problems.\">Testing and Debugging</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d215e1_d216e1_d217e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If applicable, integrate other third-part components, such as web services or .NET components. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"juz1692183224178.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/juz1692183224178.html\" title=\"The Uniface architecture enables you to integrate Uniface and non-Uniface components in a single application, and to deploy the application on a large variety of platforms and technologies.\">Integrating with Other Technologies</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gkr1665702760703__li_d218e1_d219e1_d220e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Deploy the application on your preferred platform. You can copy the deployment archives to the appropriates hosts and edit configuration files to configure the application for your environment. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ofu1665702741888.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ofu1665702741888.html\" title=\"Deploying a Uniface application entails installing the Uniface runtime servers in the appropriate locations, distributing the application runtime objects to the most effective locations in the infrastructure, and editing the configuration files so that the Uniface runtime environment can locate the required resources.\">Deploying Applications</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zhr1665702742172.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zhr1665702742172.html\" title=\"Deploying a Uniface enterprise application is largely a matter of configuring the environment to ensure that all components are running in the appropriate locations and that Uniface is able to find them. Configuration files ensure that the Uniface runtime environment can locate and initialize the application components correctly.\">Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications</a>.\n            </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527897\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527897\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Developing Applications with Uniface Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Developing Applications with Uniface Use the Uniface IDE to create development objects, and then build them into Uniface archive files that are immediately deployed into a standalone test environment. Developing applications is an iterative process, so the following steps provide a high-level guide to the activities involved in developing a Uniface application. Start by creating a Project to hold the Development Objects for your application. For more information, see Working with Projects . Create some Modeled Entities to define the application data and default behavior. These can then be reused in the components you create in the next step. For more information, see Modeling the Application . Construct the application components for the user interface and business logic. For more information, see Constructing Components and Other Objects . The type of components you need depend on the type of application. For web and mobile applications, use Dynamic Server Pages for the user interface and Services to handle backend processing. For more information, see Developing Web Applications and Developing Mobile Apps . For desktop applications, us Form components for the user interface, Report components for printing, and Service components for business logic. For more information, see Developing Desktop Applications . If necessary, create an Application Shell. For more information, see Application Shells . Build the application files. In the Project Editor of your project, click Compile . This process automatically compiles components and library definitions and may package them into a deployable archive file (depending on your configuration). For more information, see Compilation . Debug the application. The IDE includes a pre-configured deployment environment that you can use for unit testing and a Debugger to analyze problems. For more information, see Testing and Debugging . If applicable, integrate other third-part components, such as web services or .NET components. For more information, see Integrating with Other Technologies . Deploy the application on your preferred platform. You can copy the deployment archives to the appropriates hosts and edit configuration files to configure the application for your environment. For more information, see Deploying Applications and Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}